OL,4,G````````````B PRIMARY G``````Su;/!G````
OL,5,BSUMMER HOLIDAYSGby Joanne, 11,         
OL,6,GHighcliffe Primary School, Birstall.   
OL,8,COn the beach or around the pool        
OL,9,CThe sun shall shimmer like a jewel.    
OL,11,CAlong the shingle at the dusk of day   
OL,12,CThe sun putting his hat away.          
OL,14,CStanding on the pier out at sea,       
OL,15,CIn the mystical water, a reflection    
OL,16,Cof me!                                 
OL,18,CThe summer holidays disappear          
OL,19,CPreparing the agenda for next year.    
